    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Blame Game</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mike Saelens letter discusses fact that New York Yankees and New York Mets have never had minority manager (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>I agree wholeheartedly with Reggie Jackson that Willie Randolph is long overdue for a manager's job.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>I agree wholeheartedly with Reggie Jackson that Willie Randolph is long overdue for a manager's job.</p>
        <p>But I have two problems with Jackson's statements. First, Randolph has never managed; it's not as easy as it looks. Second, putting that aside, why is Jackson coming down so hard on franchises like Detroit, Milwaukee and Tampa Bay? They've all had minority group members as managers in the past. When have either the Yankees or the Mets had a minority manager? So, to Reggie and all the smug, self-satisfied New Yorkers who think that the world begins and ends on their doorsteps, there is indeed life outside New York, believe it or not.</p>
        <p>MIKE SAELENS  Chicago</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
